# SEQR

For testing hail performance with seqr.


## Installing SEQR

    $ git clone git@github.com:broadinstitute/seqr.git
    $ ln -s seqr/hail_search .


## Getting the Data

Need access to the following buckets:
- seqr-reference-data
- seqr-hail-search-data

Then

    $ mkdir -p data/GRCh38/SNV_INDEL/families
    $ pushd data/GRCh38/SNV_INDEL/

    $ export PREFIX="seqr-hail-search-data/v03/GRCh38/SNV_INDEL" && \
      gsutil -m cp -r "gs://$PREFIX/annotations.ht" . && \
      gsutil -m cp -r "gs://$PREFIX/families/F041731_rgp_2436.ht" familes/

    $ export PREFIX="seqr-reference-data/v03/GRCh38/SNV_INDEL/cached_reference_dataset_queries" && \
      gsutil -m cp -r "gs://$PREFIX/clinvar_path_variants.ht" . && \
      gsutil -m cp -r "gs://$PREFIX/high_af_variants.ht" .

    $ popd

For now, we can use the dummy data from seqr/hail_search/fixtures as they're
not used:

    $ ln -s hail_search/fixtures/GRCh38/MITO data/GRCh38/MITO
    $ ln -s hail_search/fixtures/GRCh38/SV_WES data/GRCh38/SV_WES
    $ ln -s hail_search/fixtures/GRCh38/SV_WGS data/GRCh38/SV_WGS


## Usage
See help output for usage:

    $ DATASETS_DIR=$PWD/data ./run.py --help


## Query payloads
`run.py` discovers query payload `.json` files in the `query/` folder.
You can add your favourite payloads there.
Hidden files (ie those whose name starts with '.') are excluded.
